# Docker daemon vulnerabilities (AuthZ plugin bypass, plugin privilege off-by-one).
# These CVEs can be triggered by client access or user actions against the daemon.
# Suppression is conditional on:
#   - The testcontainers-go daemon is isolated from untrusted network access
#   - No untrusted plugins are installed in test or CI environments
# This project uses github.com/docker/docker as an indirect dependency
# (via testcontainers-go for integration tests and golang-migrate for DB migrations).
# Docker v29 fix (29.3.1) is not available as a Go module tag (module path
# changed to github.com/moby/moby/v2). No backport exists for v28.x.
# Re-evaluate when docker/docker publishes v29+ Go module tags.
CVE-2026-34040 exp:2026-06-30
CVE-2026-33997 exp:2026-06-30
